        'absit invidia': { d: 'let ill will/envy be absent', m: 'Said in the context of a statement of excellence: unlike the English expression no offense, absit invidia is intended to ward off envious deities who might interpret a statement of excellence as hubris. Also extended to absit invidia verbo, (may ill will/envy be absent from these words). Contrast it with absit iniuria verbis. An explanation of Livys usage.'},
