        'aetatis suae': { d: 'of his age (followed by an ordinal number)', m: 'Thus, at the age of _ [years]. Appears on portraits, gravestones, monuments, et cetera. Usually preceded by anno (AAS), in the year [of his age/life] _. Sometimes shortened to aetatis, aetat., or even aet. Frequently combined with Anno Domini, giving a date as both the theoretical age of Jesus Christ and the age of the decedent; e. g., Obiit anno Domini MDCXXXVIo (tricensimo sexto), [anno] aetatis suae XXVo (vicensimo quinto) (he died in the 1636th year of the Lord, [being] the 25th [year] of his age[/life]).'},
